In this article, Melania Trump reflects on the past year and addresses the events at the Capitol on January 6, 2021. She expresses her condolences for the individuals who lost their lives, including Ashli Babbitt, Benjamin Philips, Kevin Greeson, Roseanne Boyland, Brian Sicknick, and Howard Liebengood. Melania Trump condemns the violence and calls for healing and unity in the country. She urges people to stop the violence, avoid making assumptions based on race, and focus on what unites us. Melania Trump encourages Americans to come together, show compassion, and be strong in the face of challenges. She thanks the supporters of her and her husband, and expresses gratitude for the opportunity to serve as First Lady. Melania Trump concludes by asking for healing, grace, understanding, and peace for the United States of America.